@alpha 0.1.0:
        All code has been refactored,
        and the project directory structure is now as follows:
                .
                ├── main.c      / main program /
                ├── apr.h       / all types and function declarations /
                ├── output.c    / all output functions /
                ├── parser.c    / all parsing functions /
                └── utils.c     / all utility functions */

        The refactored code structure is now highly modularized,
        ensuring a clean separation of concerns and superior readability.

        It is also ready to support more file formats beyond .c files via the pmod[] mapping.

        furthermore, the '--chmap' mode display has been optimized and renamed
        to '--unimap' mode to better reflect its functionality.

        A true ascii-based mode will be developed shortly.

@alpha 0.0.5:
        Optimized the display of the '--list' mode:
        * Refactored the entire 'list_print()';
        * it now looks much more aesthetic.

        Refactored the parsing logic of parse:
        * 'rt.comments' is now a 'char **'.

@alpha 0.0.4:
        Optimized the display of the '--chmap' mode.

@alpha 0.0.3:
        The '--chmap' mode is now available for printing heatmaps to the terminal.
        Fixed some silly mistakes in help().

@alpha 0.0.2:
        Added a simple bash script 'make.sh' for compilation.
        Improved the help() function,
        so now 'apr --help' can be used to print the entire list of commands.

